President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Robert M. Speer is nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Army for Financial Management at the Department of Defense. Jonathan Nicholas Stivers is nominated for Assistant Administrator of the Bureau for Asia at the United States Agency for International Development. Ramin Toloui is nominated for Deputy Under Secretary for International Finance at the Department of the Treasury, and upon appointment, will be designated Assistant Secretary for International Finance. Alice G. Wells is nominated for Ambassador to the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan at the Department of State. Additionally, President Obama intends to appoint Rabbi Lee T. Bycel as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council, Mostafa A. El-Sayed as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Stephen R. Gephard as a Commissioner of the Council of the North Atlantic Salmon Conservation Organization, Patrick C. Keliher as a Commissioner of the Council of the North Atlantic Salmon Conservation Organization, and Daniel S. Morris as a Commissioner of the Council of the North Atlantic Salmon Conservation Organization. President Obama expresses his gratitude to these individuals for their willingness to serve the American people.